name: Silk Road

I asked about the ladies' room and the cashier pointed to the corridor, and specifically mentioned there was not a ladies' room, but 'two washrooms, for customers'. Both were marked 'washroom' with no gender specified.
comment: Probably step-free or one small step to get into restaurant, but do not recall any other accessibility features. Restaurant is very new, will check back re changing tables etc. Food is Afghan-style kebabs and is excellent!

name: Holy Cross Hall, Saint Mary's College, The Avenue, South Bend, IN 46616, USA
directions: On the “basement” floor on the main hall. If you’re facing the health center it’ll be the third door to the right from the opposite end with the door.
comment:
You need a student ID or help from someone who does to get into this part of the building. 
You have to look right at the door to see its sign, you could walk right past it and never notice. 

If you are using a wheelchair, there is a side door in the building that opens directly into the right floor. There is a door opener button then a ramp down. The main entrance isn’t accessible. If you need to use at night, be aware that that door is on lockdown after around 8pm, you’ll need someone inside to let you in.
